<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[670,1199,493,1132]" pageId="28" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1867" box="[699,828,493,516]" class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Peropteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[699,828,493,516]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="28">Peropteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Peters, 1868" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1868" box="[889,1020,493,516]" class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Peronymus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[889,1020,493,516]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="28">Peronymus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been traditionally recognized as distinct genera (e.g., Miller, 1907; Sanborn, 1937; 
<bibRefCitation author="Husson, A. M." bookContentInfo="282 pp." box="[1027,1193,552,575]" journalOrPublisher="Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" refId="ref95767" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52: 282 pp. 1 30 pls." title="The bats of Suriname" type="book" year="1962">Husson, 1962</bibRefCitation>
, 1978), and many recent authors have continued to treat them as such (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Brosset, A. &amp; P. Charles-Dominique" journalOrPublisher="Mammalia" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" pagination="509 - 559" part="54" refId="ref91807" refString="Brosset, A., and P. Charles-Dominique 1990. The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach. Mammalia 54: 509 - 559." title="The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach" type="journal article" year="1990">Brosset and CharlesÂ­Dominique, 1990</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Peters, 1868" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1868" class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Peronymus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="28">Peronymus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1867" box="[821,950,669,692]" class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Peropteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[821,950,669,692]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="28">Peropteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share a unique morphology of the antebrachial wing sac (Sanborn, 1937; 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones, J. K. &amp; C. S. Hood" bookContentInfo="32 pp." box="[812,1075,728,751]" journalOrPublisher="Occas. Pap. Mus. Texas Tech Univ" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" refId="ref96227" refString="Jones, J. K., and C. S. Hood 1993. Synopsis of South American bats of the family Emballonuridae. Occas. Pap. Mus. Texas Tech Univ. 155: 32 pp." title="Synopsis of South American bats of the family Emballonuridae" type="book" year="1993">Jones and Hood, 1993</bibRefCitation>
), and phylogenetic studies have shown that these taxa form a monophyletic group (
<bibRefCitation author="Griffiths, T. A. &amp; A. L. Smith" journalOrPublisher="Bull. Am. Mus. Nat. Hist." pageId="28" pageNumber="28" pagination="62 - 83" part="206" refId="ref94734" refString="Griffiths, T. A., and A. L. Smith 1991. Systematics of emballonuroid bats (Chiroptera: Emballonuridae and Rhinopomatidae), based on hyoid morphology. Bull. Am. Mus. Nat. Hist. 206: 62 - 83." title="Systematics of emballonuroid bats (Chiroptera: Emballonuridae and Rhinopomatidae), based on hyoid morphology" type="journal article" year="1991">Griffiths and Smith, 1991</bibRefCitation>
). Indeed, the principal distinguishing character of 
<taxonomicName authority="Peters, 1868" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1868" baseAuthorityName="W.Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[925,1199,845,868]" class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Peronymus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucopterus">
<emphasis box="[925,1199,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="28">Peronymus leucopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the only species referred to the genus) is its white wing membranes, which are clearly autapomorphic. Accordingly, we follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Cabrera, A." bookContentInfo="307 pp." journalOrPublisher="Rev. Museo Argent. Cienc. Nat. '' Bernardino Rivadavia' ' (Cienc. Zool.) 4" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" refId="ref91973" refString="Cabrera, A. 1958. Catalogo de los mamiferos de America del Sur. Rev. Museo Argent. Cienc. Nat. '' Bernardino Rivadavia' ' (Cienc. Zool.) 4 (1): 307 pp." title="Catalogo de los mamiferos de America del Sur" type="book" year="1958">Cabrera (1958)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones, J. K. &amp; C. S. Hood" bookContentInfo="32 pp." box="[843,1137,962,985]" journalOrPublisher="Occas. Pap. Mus. Texas Tech Univ" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" refId="ref96227" refString="Jones, J. K., and C. S. Hood 1993. Synopsis of South American bats of the family Emballonuridae. Occas. Pap. Mus. Texas Tech Univ. 155: 32 pp." title="Synopsis of South American bats of the family Emballonuridae" type="book" year="1993">Jones and Hood (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Koopman, K. F." box="[670,866,992,1015]" editor="D. E. Wilson &amp; D. M. Reeder" journalOrPublisher="Washington, DC: Smithson. Inst. Press" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" refId="ref96667" refString="1993. Order Chiroptera. In D. E. Wilson and D. M. Reeder (eds.), Mammal species of the World, a taxonomic and geographic reference, 2 nd ed.: 137 - 241. Washington, DC: Smithson. Inst. Press." title="Order Chiroptera" type="book" volumeTitle="Mammal species of the World, a taxonomic and geographic reference, 2 nd" year="1993">Koopman (1993</bibRefCitation>
, 1994) in regarding 
<taxonomicName authority="Peters, 1868" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1868" class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Peronymus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="28">Peronymus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1867" box="[1030,1159,1021,1044]" class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Peropteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1030,1159,1021,1044]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="28">Peropteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A useful key to the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1867" box="[1030,1159,1051,1074]" class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Peropteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1030,1159,1051,1074]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="28">Peropteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
so defined was provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones, J. K. &amp; C. S. Hood" bookContentInfo="32 pp." journalOrPublisher="Occas. Pap. Mus. Texas Tech Univ" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" refId="ref96227" refString="Jones, J. K., and C. S. Hood 1993. Synopsis of South American bats of the family Emballonuridae. Occas. Pap. Mus. Texas Tech Univ. 155: 32 pp." title="Synopsis of South American bats of the family Emballonuridae" type="book" year="1993">Jones and Hood (1993)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
